items.Video_Title: How To Clean White Leather Sneakers - New Balance 550
items.Video_Description:
How To Clean White Leather Sneakers - New Balance 550
Welcome back to another episode of Shoe Care Academy with Jonny Bubbles. Today we’re rocking with one of the most popular sneakers of 2021-2022, the New Balance 550. 

Megell didn’t get these all-white New Balance 550’s dirty enough, so Jonny took the liberty and wrecked them even more.

items.Video_Title: Unboxing & First Look: New Balance 550 White/Grey
ASICS EX89 vs NEW BALANCE 550: Which Sneaker is Right for You?
items.Video_Description:
In this video I’m going to review and on foot the new Asics EX89 and compare it to the New Balance 550.. You might not like what I’ve got to say, so stick around to the end aaaaaand LETS GO! “And here they are, the “BOSTON CELTICS”Standard Asics box, shame as they could have done something a bit more retro.Official Name is: EX89 White/French Blue (is that another way of saying GREEN??) These are unofficially the “BOSTON CELTICS” and released in a pack alongside the Knicks and Lakers.Prior to that Kith already released a set as part of their 2022 A/W Collection!

Shoe Story

The EX89 sneaker blends the heritage influences of the GEL-EXTREME basketball shoe from 1989 with modern cushioning properties.
It was originally created by Toshikazu Kayano in the late 1980s as his first design project with ASICS. The upper leather construction is also met with spirited color blocking that matches the eras iconic NBA team uniforms.
Asics updated the cushioning system with their FF BLAST technology. Thats met with a sculpted heel shape to improve underfoot comfort during everyday scenarios.The outsoles pattern is meant to mirror the view of a city from the sky. This functional grip feature was initially inspired by the designers first business trip to the United States in 1987.

Shoe Details

Feels well made and quite weighty!
I’ve swapped out the laces to match the midsole.
Nice padded tongue. Good quality leather, that will age nicely.
The Celtic Green LINING, sets it off and just the right amount of - its got character but it's not over stated. Love the off white midsole, and why I chose this pair, and not sure what to make of the indent in the back  You get very simple asics branding on the tongue, insole and heel.

So! Let's talk about the elephant in the room, they are clearly inspired by or even a knock off of the NB550! Not only do they look very similar but the back story is almost exactly the same.Teddy Santis from Aime Leon Dore, said he found a clipping of an old basketball ad that featured the 550’s from the early 80’s. So they brought them back for an ALD collaboration, which went crazy and now everyone’s wearing them.And supposedly Ronnie Fieg found the Gel-Extreme’s in the Asics Archives which they reimagined into this EX89 and launched as a Kith collab..Which defo sets off my bullshit radar!.. I think this started in a board room at Asics, with a white board with the statement, WHAT HAS nEW balance done to create this recent success… and eventually we get to this!

The similarities and glaringly obvious.The silhouette is almost identical and just the leather paneling is arranged slightly differently. The main difference is the experience on foot, I have to say the 550, feels more secure and padded, while leaving enough room for my toes.It might just be this ALD pair, but the quality of materials and build actually feels really premium.. BUT I doubt that's the case for the rest of the GR’s

I prefer the look and feel of the 550.. BUT its completely played out and on every hipster, with a MacBook drinking an oat vanilla latte.
While the EX89’s give me the same aesthetic, but not seen or even really known at this point. So if I had to pick one to wear right now - its the EX89. But I have a feeling they are going to flood the market, so I better get my steps in!!

items.Video_Title: My New Balance 550 collection✍️
New Balance 550 Triple Black In Hand Review
How To Clean New Balance 550
items.Video_Description:
#SneakerLAB #NewBalance #newbalance550 

We got our hands on a dirty pair of New Balance 550 sneakers and we thought to document the cleaning process to show you the best way to look after your sneakers. The 550 was originally released in 1989 with the 550 following the industry’s trend of brands offering a low-top counterpart to their marquee hoops-ready footwear. This basketball sneaker then received a new lease of life through Aimé Leon Dore’s (ALD) drop of the 550. On September 21st 2020, Teddy Santis, ALD’s founder shifted the trajectory of both New Balance and ALD by unveiling four colorways of the 550 and it has since become a must have for all sneakerheads around the globe.

Sneaker LAB is excited to announce our partnership with New Balance in the Asia-Pacific regions. Now you can purchase your favourite Sneaker LAB products while you’re shopping for the latest pair of New Balance sneakers. Find out more here.

We used the products found in our Premium Kit and our Leather Care to clean and look after this pair. The Premium Kit consists of our Sneaker Cleaner, Sneaker Protector, Odor Protector and Premium Brush.

Step 1: 
﻿First you will need to prepare your shoes for a deep clean! Remove the laces from the shoes and set them aside as you will clean those at a later stage. Grab our Premium Brush and dry brush off any excess dirt that may be laying on the surface of the shoe.

Step 2:
Spray Sneaker Cleaner around the uppers of the sneakers and focus on the heavily dirtied areas. Then grab our Premium Brush and then dip into a container of water. Start scrubbing in a circular motion. The water and Sneaker Cleaner solution will react together creating a form that will remove the dirt on the sneakers. On this particular model of 550, the majority of the sneaker is made up of leather but there are mesh panels that will need more attention when cleaning. Use more Sneaker Cleaner on these areas, and dip the Premium Brush into water and scrub in a circular motion. This process may need repeating to lift out the dirt that has embedded itself into material.

Step 3:
You will then turn your attention to the soles of the sneakers - you can follow the same process as before but can use more force if necessary to remove any stubborn dirt on the soles of the sneakers. 

Step 4:
We then used our Sneaker Wipes to do spot cleans and touch ups on those hard to reach places. The wipes provide a convenient way of scrubbing away dirt on materials like mesh.

Step 5:
Use our Microfiber Towel to dry off the excess moisture and the last remaining dirt. Next, you will set your sneakers aside to dry. 

Step 6:
Whilst your sneakers are drying, you can start cleaning the laces. You will cup the laces in your hand and spray Sneaker Cleaner onto them. Strat rubbing them together in your hands and then dip into a clean container of water. Continue this process until the dirt is visibly removed. Use a Microfiber Towel to ring out the excess moisture and set aside to dry with your sneakers.

Step 7:
When your sneakers and laces are dry, you can do your laces up on the sneakers. 

Step 8:
Next we will add our protective products. Firstly, use our Odor Protector to remove unwanted odors and prevent bad bacteria from building. If the inner soles are removable, take them out and spray the inside of the sneaker and the inner soles. 

Step 9:
Next, use our Leather Care on the leather sections of this specific 550. If your 550s don't have leather you can skip this step. Leather Care will protect and nourish the leather panels and will prevent cracking.

Step 10:

Lastly, you will apply Sneaker Protector to the mesh, tongue and laces of the sneakers to create an invisible barrier against dirt and stains. This will also make cleaning easier in the future as it will prevent dirt from setting in.

Step 11:

Wear your shoes! 

Thank you for watching and let us know what you think of the video in the comments below!

items.Video_Title: UNBOXING THE NEW BALANCE 550 CREAM/BLACK - THE BEST COLOURWAY YET?!
items.Video_Description:
Take an early look at one of the hottest New Balance releases of the year, the New Balance 550 “Cream/Black” 🔥 

The NB550 has been one of the most popular silhouettes of the year, instantly flying off the shelves as soon as it releases, and we don’t see this release being any different. Featuring a minimalistic colour palette, the cream upper is complimented by an aged midsole, perfectly on trend for any vintage-inspired looks. Contrasting pops of black are then featured on the midsole and ankle. 

What makes this 550 really stand out is the attention to detail. The iconic New Balance ‘N’ logo is finished with a basketball-leather, paying homage to the sneakers roots as a basketball shoe in the 80s. The tongue then also features a mesh material for added breathability, which also compliments the textured leather upper. 

With its vintage design and similarities to the Aimé Leon Dore collabs, the New Balance 550 “Cream/Black” is bound to be a sell-out hit. Set to drop on May 24th for a retail price of £100, you’re not gonna want to miss out. Make sure you click the link below and turn on release reminders for the best chance to cop!
